Today the NHBRC has temporarily closed down its Tzaneen satellite office after an employee tested positive for COVID-19.  The office will resume with its normal operations on Monday, 6 July 2020. Developers, contractors, home builders and housing consumers in the area are advised to use the Polokwane and/or Thulamela offices. “As part of our precautionary measures, all the affected employees based in that office will also be in self-isolation for a period of 14 days as per the COVID-19 regulations,” said NHBRC Acting CEO Otsile Maseng. We further urge the developers, contractors, home builders and housing consumers, to only visit our offices when it is absolutely necessary for collection of certificates (i.e. registration and enrolment) and to complete technical assessments. Customers who need to submit necessary supporting documents are encouraged to do so from the safety of their homes or offices via our new emailing list on the following contact address; Province Registrations, Renewals, Enrolments, Complaints and Collections of Certificates Inspections Limpopo LP-online@nhbrc.org.zadocument.getElementById('cloakdcb46ccc36e41209b76a0ae32b721075').innerHTML='';var prefix='&#109;a'+'i&#108;'+'&#116;o';var path='hr'+'ef'+'=';var addydcb46ccc36e41209b76a0ae32b721075='LP-&#111;nl&#105;n&#101;'+'&#64;';addydcb46ccc36e41209b76a0ae32b721075=addydcb46ccc36e41209b76a0ae32b721075+'nhbrc'+'&#46;'+'&#111;rg'+'&#46;'+'z&#97;';var addy_textdcb46ccc36e41209b76a0ae32b721075='LP-&#111;nl&#105;n&#101;'+'&#64;'+'nhbrc'+'&#46;'+'&#111;rg'+'&#46;'+'z&#97;';document.getElementById('cloakdcb46ccc36e41209b76a0ae32b721075').innerHTML+='<a '+path+'\''+prefix+':'+addydcb46ccc36e41209b76a0ae32b721075+'\'>'+addy_textdcb46ccc36e41209b76a0ae32b721075+'<\/a>'; LPinspections@nhbrc.org.zadocument.getElementById('cloak697b8171cb6ef76610b4fd74e906cdcd').innerHTML='';var prefix='&#109;a'+'i&#108;'+'&#116;o';var path='hr'+'ef'+'=';var addy697b8171cb6ef76610b4fd74e906cdcd='LP&#105;nsp&#101;ct&#105;&#11